[normal]the actions to be taken in response to this recommendation
[normal]h.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Provision of barriers at higher risk locally monitored automatic open crossings (reports 16/2010, Halkirk: published September 2010 and 12/2011, AOCLs: published July 2011).
[normal]Halkirk level 
[normal]crossing, the site of an accident in which three occupants of a road vehicle were killed has been upgraded by the installation of half barriers (reference rec 3 of report 16/2010, Halkirk).
[normal]Network Rail is implementing a programme to upgrade its highest ri
[normal]sk AOCLs.  The project is looking to upgrade about 72 (including all in 
[normal]Scotland
[normal]) out of 110 AOCL crossings in total.  The upgrade consists of adding a modular barrier system to an existing AOCL level crossing.  Prototype installations are presently being 
[normal]trialled.  
[normal]The RAIB is keen to understand the outcome of these trials and the programme of ongoing installation.
[normal]i.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Digital red light enforcement equipment (report 12/2011, AOCLs: published July 2011).
[normal]The British Transport Police, in consultation with Network Rail, has introduced a fleet of level crossing enforcement vans.  
[normal]The RAIB is keen to understand the impact of this initiative on levels of road user violation.
[normal]j.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Steps to improve the brightness 
[normal]of road traffic signals at level crossings to improve their conspicuity in bright sunlight (Beech Hill, Dec 2012).
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The RAIB report is due to be published within the next month.
[normal]Risk management
[normal]k.
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Actions to improve the accuracy and consistency of data 
[normal]collected at level crossings during site visits and a review of the organisational arrangements for the assessment of risk, including the appointment of dedicated level crossing managers (various reports including 14/2011, Sudbury: published Aug 2011).
[normal]Imp
[normal]roved guidance on assessing local factors, and taking account of the history of previous incidents, when assessing risk at level crossings (report 16/2010, Halkirk: published September 2010)
[normal]Network Rail has reported that it has a broad programme of 
[normal]initiatives aimed at improving the safety of crossings, including a revision of how crossings will be risk assessed; closures of high risk crossings; the upgrade of equipment; the recruitment and training of staff dedicated to crossing safety management; a
[normal]nd improved asset knowledge and information management.  Network Rail intends that individual managers will take full responsibility for the safety of each crossing and will develop a detailed appreciation of the safety issues at each.
[normal]The RAIB supports th
[normal]e initiative and awaits with interest Network Rail’s evaluation of the affect on the quality of level crossing management.
